The paper deals with capacity regions of linear deterministic networks, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves interference neutralization and zero forcing, which are techniques used in network coding (cs.NI) and network engineering (cs.NE). The paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of signal processing (cs.SI) and computer communications (cs.CC) due to its focus on communication networks.
